<p>For the 1-hour drop-in map workshop at <a href="https://tanaudel.wordpress.com/2022/05/09/brisbane-writers-festival-2022-very-brief-recap/">BWF</a>, I made little zine-fold (aka 8-fold) booklets, which I put in little mermaid-stamped envelopes with little pencils and little pieces of nice drawing paper. (I think I learned this in primary school, but there are plenty of instructions for this sort of booklet online, e.g. <a href="https://www.wikihow.com/Make-a-Zine">wikiHow</a>.)</p>



<p>Above, you can see the mock-up process (the easiest way to turn a vague idea into something real: <a href="https://tanaudel.wordpress.com/2020/03/12/making-things-manifest-mock-ups-and-outlines/">Mockups and outlines</a>).</p>



