}" data-image-title="lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=1024" src="https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-29" width="492" height="492" srcset="https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=492 492w, https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=984 984w, https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=150 150w, https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=300 300w, https://time7219310.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/lb0128-03-working-at-home-tips-get-rid-of-distractions.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 492px) 100vw, 492px" /></figure>



<ol start="4" class="has-large-font-size"><li>Taking Breaks </li></ol>



<p style="font-style:italic;font-weight:500;">Always pushing away distractions will allow you to get more done than ever before, but this isn’t realistic. It could take a toll on your mental health if you never allow yourself to enjoy your distractions occasionally. However, this doesn’t mean when you get distracted, just drop what you’re doing and leave it as a future problem. Breaks can motivate you to complete your work because you know there’s more to your day than just homework. Having designated breaks is an effective compromise from being constantly laser focused or constantly distracted. </p>



