<p>Two days before the Philippines national election day on May 9, 2022, my friends and I decided to take a little break from the grueling printing jobs we had months before the election day. Inspired by vloggers with fishing content on YouTube, we figured it would be fun to do some camping and fishing. After watching a lot of YouTube videos, we were convinced that Kamandag beach is the best place to be. We are from Dasmarinas Cavite. It was near our place and they said camping and fishing were free. We prepared our camping and fishing gear and off we went. Excited. It was Saturday, May 7, 2022. We prepared for overnight camping and fishing. It was the first time in three years since we had our outdoor experience. We heard it was a nice place to be. And most of all it was free. Or so we thought.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="54" data-permalink="https://orlyumali.wordpress.com/2022/06/11/kamandag-beach-adventure/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3/" data-orig-file="https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png" data-orig-size="1920,1080" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png?w=1024" src="https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-54" srcset="https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png?w=1024 1024w, https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png?w=150 150w, https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png?w=300 300w, https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png?w=768 768w, https://orlyumali.files.wordpress.com/2022/06/vlcsnap-2022-06-11-17h36m15s542-3.png 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>We reached Ternate, Cavite, and were met by some barangay officials there. We were asked to pay the ecological fee. Twenty pesos each to be exact. It was minimal so it was okay. A certain Robert guided us to Kamandag beach. We paid him a hundred pesos for bringing us to the site. We were unaware that the beach is privately owned and when we got there, the property caretaker asked us to pay 100 pesos each as an entrance fee, 200 pesos for each tent that we brought, and 400 pesos for the bamboo table. We paid the entrance fee and the tent fee. We did not avail of the table. It was not free after all.</p>



