<p class="has-text-align-justify">Between all of the sites, sounds and thriving people, I found myself with a blood spot behind my left eye. I wanted to believe it would go away on its own, and that it was the result of too much excitement; but I had a gnawing feeling that it was retinopathy-related. So, my friend and I made our way to the eye clinic where sure enough, I had started to bleed. This was shocking, as I had procedures before leaving the US which were meant to prevent the progression. As you can imagine I was confused, scared and a bit angry. I thought the effort I put in until that point had been wasted. But the doctors in South Korea patched me up with an injection and a warning that I would soon require further laser treatments or surgery to achieve a more permanent delay of the outcome. Later, however, I began to feel sickness in other ways. An issue arose with my wisdom teeth in which I was told I needed to remove them in order to prevent further problems. With this knowledge, I made the decision to have last-minute extraction in Korea. It was painless, and they were finished in five minutes.</p>



