<p class="has-black-color has-text-color">I had arrived early, but the kind staff accommodated me before check-in time. There was a shared kitchen and a dining area. They also offered a complimentary high tea at 4 pm, where you could interact with other travellers. They had well maintained the hostel in terms of cleanliness and hygiene. Likewise, they gave me fresh linen and a blanket to use. There were facilities such as a common hangout area with board games, charging sockets and bedside lamps for each bed, air conditioning, free Wi-Fi, concierge, in-house dining, and many more services. Breakfast, towels, laundry services, and lockers were available for separate charges. There was a well-trained staff at reception and housekeeping for 24*7 service. The hostel also conducted fun activities such as karaoke nights, city tours, game nights, etc. I realized the best part about staying in these hostels is that they are super affordable compared to conventional hotels.</p>



