<p>It was well before 11 AM when we arrived at Tipulo so we decided to have a light lunch. Coffee and dessert followed. There’s also a bakeshop on the first floor where we bought some goodies for Leo’s mom on Mother’s Day.</p>



<p>At this time of the year we would normally go island-hopping and beach-combing in other parts of the country but Leo’s current condition, while improving, means we have to limit ourselves to shorter trips. Hopefully it will improve enough for us to do much longer excursions in the months to come.</p>

