<h2><strong>Boarding </strong></h2>
<p>The aft business class cabin is massive with 11 rows of business class seats. It is airy though with no central overhead bins. The subdued lighting, beige, grey, brass, and brown tones create and warm and inviting cabin. I had read about how wide these seats are, and indeed they really are very wide. But its not as awkward as many complain.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12737" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_020833717/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_020833717.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_021923949" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_021923949.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_021923949.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12743" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_021923949.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_021923949" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_021923949.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_021923949.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_021923949.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>There are a few storage areas in the armrest/seat. The upper storage area has power outlets, and its smart of Singapore Airlines to have multiple headphone jacks, on either side of the seats. Touchscreen video monitor handset. There is also a large adjustable (height and position) tray table. One the armrest are seat controls and a do not disturb button. At the seat was a throw pillow and the care/sanitation kit, in the armrest storage was headphones and water bottle. The front of the seat houses the TV, bulkhead seats only have the mirror, regular seats have the added beverage stand. The footrest area of the bulkhead seats are their biggest selling point, so much space. This created for a comfortable sleep and space to stretch out and get comfortable.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12740" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_021606925/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_021606925.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

