<p>I was shortly brought my Singapore sling and nuts, due to COVID measures still in place, they still serve packaged instead of placing them in a saucer/plate. Small detail, but its fine.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12748" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_033906966/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_033906966.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_033906966" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_033906966.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_033906966.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12748" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_033906966.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_033906966" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_033906966.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_033906966.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_033906966.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>The flight is designed as such. First “lighter” meal service commences right after takeoff. The “main” meal service begins halfway through the flight and is offered up until 2 hours before arrival. In addition there are snacks and refreshments you can order, as well as snacks to grab from a snack basket in the galley. 1 champagne, 2 white wines, 2 reds, and a solid liquor / cocktail selection including an Aberfeldy 16 year, lots of teas and coffees to choose from. There are also a nice selection of non-alcoholic cocktails and beverages to choose from as well.</p>
<p>After post-departure beverages, the cart began to roll through with the first meal service. This was served on a tray.</p>
<p>First up was smoked trout salad and paired with an Australian chardonnay. The salad was quite good. Nice smoked trout.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12749" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_040413153/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_040413153.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

