<p>I decided to have a midflight pour of Aberfeldy 16 year. I do wish they ask if you like it on the rocks or neat, it didnt occur to me to specify neat. Not a big deal, still delicious. They even brought out more nuts to go with the whisky, which I had to decline as the second meal service was in a few hours.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12762" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_101717579/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_101717579.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_101717579" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_101717579.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_101717579.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12762" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_101717579.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_101717579" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_101717579.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_101717579.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_101717579.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>After another short nap, we hit the halfway point at 9 hours into the flight, flying over Europe, the second meal service began. They do slowly brighten the cabin lights for this service. It seemed most passengers did wake up for this meal service. It was also morning in Europe and bright outside.</p>
<p>Though this meal was still served from the carts, it was tray-less and the crew set up each tray table.</p>
<p>First up was <strong>Orange-braised baby beet salad</strong> with endive, cherry tomatoes and pine nuts. Part of a Singapore Airlines collaboration with San Diego based wellness retreat Golden Door to design wellness and healthier meals on these long flights. It was light, refreshing, a tad tangy and over all very good.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12764" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_133220515/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_133220515.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

