<p>The next few hours were spent between sleeping and watching movies. I watched a total of 4.5 films on this flight and still managed to sleep for about 8 hours. Thats how much time there is on this flight.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12759" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_100759750/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_100759750.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_100759750" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_100759750.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_100759750.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12759" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_100759750.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_100759750" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_100759750.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_100759750.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_100759750.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>Around 2 hours before arrival, I decided to have myself a pre-arrival meal from the refreshments menu.</p>
<p>I started off with a Non alcoholic cocktail: <strong>Apple Bliss</strong>: bitter lemon soda, sprite and apple juice. Very tasty, never thought to mix apple juice with bitter lemon soda.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12769" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_190832127/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_190832127.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_190832127" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_190832127.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_190832127.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12769" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_190832127.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_190832127" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_190832127.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_190832127.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_190832127.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>I ordered <strong>Rice noodles with braised pork belly and vegetables</strong>. The pork belly was so flavorful and melt in your mouth. The broth was rich and soothing. What a lovely meal.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12770" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_191905771/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_191905771.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_191905771" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_191905771.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_191905771.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12770" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_191905771.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_191905771" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_191905771.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_191905771.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_191905771.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>After I changed out of my PJs and walked by the galley, the crew asked me if I needed anything else, and I asked for a cup of Guatemala single origin coffee before landing. We hit some heavy turbulence right after so they came out and apologized that my coffee would be delayed as they cannot serve hot beverages during turbulence and it was heavy enough that they had to be seated. A few minutes later I was served the wonderful cup of coffee.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12771" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_205823584/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_205823584.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_233416754" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_233416754.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_233416754.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12775" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_233416754.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_233416754" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_233416754.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_233416754.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_233416754.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>At first, I sat there not knowing how to order or who to order with. The owner, one-man show, told me to hold on a minute, but I saw more and more people come in and they just all ordered directly with the man. I thus got up and placed my order directly with him. In true Singaporean fashion, you can order in English, Mandarin or Hokkien, though Mandarin and Hokkien preferred. Cash ONLY.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12772" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_230040620/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_230040620.jpeg" data-orig-size="1080,608" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

