<p>I ordered <strong>Butter Kopi,</strong> coffee with condensed milk and butter, very tasty, butter was not salty but adds a creamy textured. Soft boiled egg with soy sauce and white pepper, and<strong> Kaya Toast.</strong></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12774" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220505_232341089/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_232341089.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220505_232341089" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_232341089.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_232341089.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12774" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_232341089.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220505_232341089" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_232341089.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_232341089.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220505_232341089.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>Following breakfast, I ordered a Grab to head to <strong>Jewel Changi.</strong> Sadly I was too early and the waterfall featured was not turned on yet. But it really is such an amazing place to visit and really does live up to the hype. Beautifully designed.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12776" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220506_000328591/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_000328591.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220506_030134650" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_030134650.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_030134650.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12777" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_030134650.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220506_030134650" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_030134650.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_030134650.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_030134650.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>Singapore Airlines 787s are fitted with the airline’s regional business class, which are still in a 1-2-1 configuration and a lie flat seat, same ones used on <a href="https://gastronomictraveler.blog/2020/04/14/review-turkish-airlines-787-9-business-class-ist-atl-with-737-skd-ist/">Turkish Airlines 787s</a> , which are truly a tad narrow. But for regional flights from 4-6 hours, perfectly comfortable.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12778" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220506_032520966/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032520966.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220506_032520966" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032520966.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032520966.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12778" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032520966.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220506_032520966" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032520966.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032520966.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032520966.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>I was warmly welcomed by the crew. The business cabin had only 7 passengers including myself to 3 crew. What a great ratio. I was walked to my seat and offered an pre-departure beverage, and even offered to have my picture taken as the flight attendant saw me snapping away. I opted for some Charles Heidsieck champagne.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12780" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220506_033450657/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_033450657.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220506_033450657" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_033450657.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_033450657.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12780" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_033450657.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220506_033450657" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_033450657.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_033450657.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_033450657.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>At my seat was a pillow, blanket (regional style, not as plush or large as the longhaul ones), water bottle, headset in the storage unit and sanitation/care kit.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12779" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220506_032534341/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032534341.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220506_032534341" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032534341.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032534341.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12779" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032534341.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220506_032534341" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032534341.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032534341.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_032534341.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>The flight attendant came by shortly to introduce themselves and confirm my Book the cook order of the famous Lobster Thermidor as well as take my post-departure beverage order. The beverage list was near identical to the SQ23 longhaul one, which is nice to see.</p>
<p>Soon doors were closed and we were off, and interestingly we departed from a newish? or newly connected runway that normally hosts the Singapore Airshow, as the other main runway was under repairs.</p>
<p>First thing’s first, Singapore Sling.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="12781" data-permalink="http://gastronomictraveler.blog/2022/05/15/review-worlds-longest-flight-on-singapore-airlines-sq23-jfk-sin-in-business-class/pxl_20220506_041528286/" data-orig-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_041528286.jpeg" data-orig-size="368,654" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="PXL_20220506_041528286" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_041528286.jpeg?w=169" data-large-file="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_041528286.jpeg?w=368" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12781" src="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_041528286.jpeg" alt="PXL_20220506_041528286" width="368" height="654" srcset="https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_041528286.jpeg 368w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_041528286.jpeg?w=84&h=150 84w, https://garythegastronomictraveler.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/pxl_20220506_041528286.jpeg?w=169&h=300 169w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>I think given the light load, there was no cart service. They simply delivered each person’s tray directly to them. Throughout the meal service they kept coming through to offer water refills, ask to refill wine / cocktails and bread as well. Amazing.</p>
<p>First up, Giant lump crab salad with spiced mango, super good, and a glass of Bordeaux. The salad was refreshing with a nice dash of spice and zest.</p>
