<p>Three cheers for The Nest’s Sunday time killer known as the Weekend Threesome!  Three oddball bits from the past week I thought you should know about…</p>
<p><a href="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg"><img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="22241" data-permalink="http://evilsquirrelsnest.com/2021/05/02/weekend-threesome-5-2-21/threesome-one/" data-orig-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg" data-orig-size="600,164" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="threesome one" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg?w=600" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-22241" src="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="164" srcset="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg 600w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg?w=150&h=41 150w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-one.jpg?w=300&h=82 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a></p>
<p>I enjoyed a nice five day respite from work this week before going back last night.  But before that, I still had to work last weekend, and I took my first break Sunday night on our lawn and garden patio.</p>
<p><div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_6819" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/07/possums012.jpg"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-6819" data-attachment-id="6819" data-permalink="http://evilsquirrelsnest.com/2015/07/29/a-marsupial-mecca/possums012/" data-orig-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/07/possums012.jpg" data-orig-size="1216,912" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="threesome two" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-two.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-two.jpg?w=600" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-22247" src="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-two.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="149" srcset="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-two.jpg 600w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-two.jpg?w=150&h=37 150w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2021/04/threesome-two.jpg?w=300&h=75 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a></p>
<p>In the comments of <a href="https://evilsquirrelsnest.com/2022/04/30/stand-up-and-take-a-bow/">my Saturday Squirrel post from two weeks ago</a>, <a href="https://lynettedartycross.com/">Lynette</a> used the word plinth to describe the brick memorial the squirrel was standing on.  That’s a great word I hadn’t heard in ages, and as it always seems to go, I came across that word again just this past week in an amusing story from one of my bathroom readers!</p>
<p><div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_26734" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-26734" data-attachment-id="26734" data-permalink="http://evilsquirrelsnest.com/2022/04/30/stand-up-and-take-a-bow/42722squirrel028/" data-orig-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,750" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="42722squirrel028" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="<p>A squirrel on his plinth.</p>
" data-medium-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg?w=1000" class="size-large wp-image-26734" src="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg?w=640" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg?w=640 640w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg?w=150 150w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg?w=300 300w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg?w=768 768w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2022/04/42722squirrel028.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-26734" class="wp-caption-text">A squirrel on his plinth.</p></div></p>
<p>This snippet appeared in <em>Uncle John’s Curiously Compelling Bathroom Reader </em>under the category “Oops!” which chronicles amusing mistakes people have made, and was reprinted from the British newspaper <em>The Telegraph</em>:</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><strong><em>“One of Britain’s most prestigious art galleries put a block of slate on display, topped by a small piece of wood, in the mistaken belief it was a work of art.  The Royal Academy included the chunk of stone and the small bone-shaped wooden stick in its summer exhibition in London.  But the slate was actually a plinth — a slab on which a pedestal is placed — and the stick was designed to prop up a sculpture.  The sculpture itself — of a human head — was nowhere to be seen.  The Academy explained away the error by saying the parts were sent to the exhibition separately.  ‘Given their separate submission,’ it said in a statement, ‘the two parts were judged independently.  The head was rejected.  The base was thought to have merit and was accepted.'”</em></strong></p>
<p>Just more proof that art is always in the eye of the beholder…</p>
<p><div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_6309" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-6309" data-attachment-id="6309" data-permalink="http://evilsquirrelsnest.com/2015/04/24/statue-of-limitations/carl-barger/" data-orig-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg" data-orig-size="1024,768" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="carl barger" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="<p>Perhaps the head was Carl Barger’s… in which case, I don’t blame them for displaying the plinth.</p>
" data-medium-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg?w=1024" class="size-large wp-image-6309" src="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg?w=640" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg?w=640 640w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg?w=150 150w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg?w=300 300w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg?w=768 768w, https://evilsquirrelsnest.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/carl-barger.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-6309" class="wp-caption-text">Perhaps <a href="https://evilsquirrelsnest.com/2018/11/23/39-off-with-his-head/">the head was Carl Barger’s</a>… in which case, I don’t blame them for displaying the plinth.</p></div></p>
