<p>Pr stay – We we’re absolutely honoured to be given the opportunity to work with Crerar Hotels for a 2 night stay at the Oban Bay Hotel. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="516" data-permalink="https://thehighlandmummy.wordpress.com/2022/05/15/oban-bay-hotel-crerar-hotels/img_6359/" data-orig-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg" data-orig-size="1920,1920" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="img_6359" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg?w=1024" src="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-516" srcset="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg?w=1024 1024w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg?w=150 150w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg?w=300 300w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg?w=768 768w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6359.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>We arrived on the Friday for our 2 night stay in the Oban bay suite. We were welcomed and offered a drink straight away by the lovely barman, Gabor and checked in within a couple of minutes and straight up to our gorgeous room. </p>



<p>Our room was breathtaking with amazing views and so many special touches from coffee machine, Scottish snacks, welcome strawberries, dressing gown and slippers, a full ice bucket with sparkling and still water, a full mini fridge and mini arran sense of Scotland body washes and a special personalised information sheet with lots of information on it. The room was huge and our son was in his element running around, jumping on the bed and sofa. The view of the bay and was perfect, so relaxing that we could have sat all night watching the world go by, especially in the bathroom as the bath was right infront of the window to appreciate the special views.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="517" data-permalink="https://thehighlandmummy.wordpress.com/2022/05/15/oban-bay-hotel-crerar-hotels/img_6329/" data-orig-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6329.jpg" data-orig-size="3024,3024" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="img_6483" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=1024" src="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-518" srcset="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=1024 1024w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=2048 2048w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=150 150w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=300 300w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6483.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>We had dinner both nights in the grill room and couldn’t find a single fault. The wait wasn’t long, the service was amazing and made us feel so at home and the food was piping hot with amazing presentation. The chef himself, Dawid came out and introduced himself and was so attentive. It was a pleasure to meet him and we wish all chefs were like him! It’s the little things that make customers want to come back and him introducing himself and checking we were happy is definitely one!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="519" data-permalink="https://thehighlandmummy.wordpress.com/2022/05/15/oban-bay-hotel-crerar-hotels/img_6057/" data-orig-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6057.jpg" data-orig-size="3024,3024" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{

}" data-image-title="img_6511" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6511.jpg?w=225" data-large-file="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6511.jpg?w=768" src="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6511.jpg?w=768" alt="" class="wp-image-533" srcset="https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6511.jpg?w=768 768w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6511.jpg?w=1536 1536w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6511.jpg?w=113 113w, https://thehighlandmummy.files.wordpress.com/2022/05/img_6511.jpg?w=225 225w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /></figure>



<p>We also had breakfast both mornings. The menu was very unique but also had your typical Scottish breakfasts which my husband had and loved every bit. We had Arran as our waiter both nights and one morning and he made us feel like we had known him for years! Very approachable and easy to chat too. He also remembered our favourite drinks which we were impressed with as there were lots of other customers!￼</p>



